  "text": "Assessments of educational attainment and age were completed in person by a trained interviewer. Participants were enrolled between 1999 and 2003. Additional information regarding the CAATSA study design can be found elsewhere [CITATION_1] . The CAATSA sample consisted of 285 pairs of twins. We dropped opposite sex fraternal twins (N = 62 pairs) to eliminate the variability in gendered access to education. We also eliminated the three twin pairs who were not raised together, (separated prior to age 13) based on other twin research with twins' socioeconomic opportunity [CITATION_2] . Finally, we dropped those who had missing data re years of education attained (N = 8). The final sample was 211 same sex twins, 99 identical and 113 fraternal.",
